          "rationale": "Pierre Berton's prose style and engaging narrative histories inspired generations of Canadians to treasure their nation's stories, and this compendium collects four of his books for younger readers in a single volume. The unknown coasts of the Arctic and the long-fabled Northwest Passage route to Asia loomed large in the nineteenth-century imagination, and this book introduces middle-grade readers to four important historical figures who shaped our modern knowledge of this region: William Edward Parry, Jane Franklin (Sir John Franklin's widow), Elisha Kent Kane, and Robert John McClure.",
